content: I've noticed you sometimes interrupt others during meetings. Allowing colleagues to finish their thoughts could improve team dynamics.
Your documentation could be more detailed. Adding examples and edge cases would help the team understand your work better.
Sometimes your messages in chat come across as abrupt. Adding more context would prevent misunderstandings.
You tend to dominate conversations in our team meetings. Creating space for others to contribute would be valuable.
Your code reviews are very thorough, but sometimes the feedback could be phrased more constructively.
I've noticed you often miss deadlines. Better time estimation and communication about delays would help the team.
Your presentations are informative but could be more engaging. Adding visuals and stories might help maintain audience attention.
You sometimes commit code without adequate testing. More thorough testing would prevent production issues.
I've noticed you don't always acknowledge others' contributions. Giving credit where it's due would boost team morale.
You tend to resist new processes and tools. Being more open to change would help your professional growth.
